OL,3,CCare sector has seen too many empty
OL,4,Cpromises
OL,6,FThere is also the not insignificant
OL,7,Frisk that Labour aren't actually in
OL,8,Fpower to deliver the reform, given
OL,9,Fthey'd need to get re-elected first.
OL,11,FMany in the sector feel the problems
OL,12,Fare already well rehearsed without the
OL,13,Fneed for yet another head-scratching
OL,14,Fexercise: under-funding, under-pay, a
OL,15,Fskills and staff shortage, the lottery
OL,16,Fof who gets council and NHS funding
OL,17,Fand who must pay out of their life
OL,18,Fsavings.
OL,20,FNone of these problems have changed in
OL,21,Fdecades, but have only become worse.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/7
