OL,3,CCare sector has seen too many empty
OL,4,Cpromises
OL,6,FIn fact, the care sector will see a
OL,7,Fsignificant rise in costs when the
OL,8,Fminimum wage and national insurance
OL,9,Fcontributions for employers both go up
OL,10,Fin the spring.
OL,12,FCarers will take on more NHS tasks
OL,13,Funder these new changes, but for no
OL,14,Fextra pay. Who incentivises them to do
OL,15,Fthat? Who pays for the training? And
OL,16,Flastly, can care providers get the
OL,17,Finsurance necessary to take on much
OL,18,Fgreater responsibility for the health
OL,19,Fof their clients?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/7
